description.p:
An embodiment, which is not part of the invention, provides an apparatus for forming a load-bearing article having a shape defining compressible core member and a thermoplastic external shell, said apparatus comprising:
a first molding tool having a first perforated surface;
a vacuum source connected to said perforations in said first molding tool for reversibly holding said core member;
a second molding tool having a convex interior surface;
a heating component for heating thermoplastics;
a first device for positioning a first thermoplastic sheet between said core member attached to said first molding tool and said concave surface of said second molding tool;
a mechanism for compressing said first sheet and said core member into contact with said concave surface of said second molding tool;
a mechanism for withdrawing said first molding tool after said first sheet is placed in contact with said second molding tool
a device for positioning a second heated thermoplastic sheet between said core member attached to first heated thermoplastic sheet and said second molding tool and said first molding tool;
a mechanism for compressing said first sheet, said core member, and said second sheet together; and
a device for welding portions of said first and second sheets in contact with one another together.

A pallet comprising:
a shape defining compressible core member, having a first core member surface, a second core member surface, and a core member perimeter, wherein said second core member surface is substantially flat, said core member first surface includes convex features, and said core member substantially determines the shape of said pallet.;
a thermoplastic shell having a shell interior and a shell edge, wherein said article is formed by a twin sheet molding process, said shell includes a first heated pliable thermoplastic sheet having an interior and a first sheet edge, said first sheet edge extending outside of said core member perimeter, and a second heated pliable thermoplastic sheet having a second sheet interior and second sheet edge extending outside of said core member perimeter, said article is formed by compressing said core member between the interiors of said first and said second sheets, and bonding the edges of said first and said second sheets to one another to form said edge of said shell, said core member is compressed within said shell formed by said first, and said core member bonds to the said interior of said shell.

The invention provides a method of forming articles including a shape defining compressible core member (30), and a thermoplastic external shell, said method comprising the steps of:
providing a shape defining compressible core member (30) including a first surface (32) and a second surface (34), wherein at least one surface (32, 34) includes a pattern of features;
positioning said core member (30) adjacent to a first heated pliable thermoplastic sheet (20) to form a stack including said first sheet (20) and said core member (30), wherein said first pliable thermoplastic sheet (20) is longer and wider than said core member (30);
compressing said stack between a first molding tool (60), and a second molding tool (90), wherein said first molding tool (60) has a surface (62) at least as long and as wide as said core member (30), and said second molding tool has a surface at least as long and as wide as said core member (30) and that said second molding tool (90) has a contour (82, 86) complementary to the features of said at least one surface (32) of said core member (30); and
holding said stack between said first and said second molding tools (60 and 90) until said stack cools and forms bonds between portions of said core member (30) and said sheet (20) while in contact with one another,
wherein the volume of a convex portion of said core member (30) is larger than the volume of a concave portion of said second molding tool complementary to the convex portion of said core member (30).

The method further comprises the steps of:
attaching said core member (30) reversible to a surface (62) of said first molding tool (60) opposing said complementary surface (82) of said second molding tool (90);
providing a first clamping frame (70) and a second clamping frame (75) wherein both said first and said second clamping frames are larger than said first and said second molding tools;
attaching said heated first thermoplastic sheet (20) to said first clamping frame (70);
positioning said first heated thermoplastic sheet (20) between said core member (30) and said complementary surface (82) of said second molding tool (90);
decreasing the distance between said first and said second molding tools (60 and 90) until said first pliable sheet (20) conforms to the contour of said features of said first surface (32) of said core member (30) and said first sheet (20) contacts said complementary surface (82) of said second molding tool (90);
releasing said core member (30) from said molding tool;
attaching a heated second thermoplastic sheet (40) to said second clamping frame (75); and
positioning said second thermoplastic sheet (40) between said first molding tool and said second surface of said core member (30) before said compressing step.

claim.claim-text:
Verfahren zur Formung eines Gegenstandes mit einem eine Form definierenden komprimierbaren Kernelement (30) und einer thermoplastischen äußeren Hülle, welches die Sehritte umfasst:
Bereitstellen eines eine Form definierenden komprimierbaren Kernelements (30) mit einer ersten Oberfläche (32) und einer zweiten Oberfläche (34), worin mindestens eine Oberfläche (32, 34) ein Muster an Merkmalen aufweist;
Positionieren des Kernelements (30) neben einer ersten erhitzten formbaren thermoplastischen Lage (20), um aus der ersten Lage (20) und dem Kernelement (30) einen Stapel zu bilden, worin die erste thermoplastische formbare Lage (20) länger und breiter ist als das Kernelement (30);
Komprimieren des Stapels zwischen einem ersten Formgebungs-Werkzeug (60) und einem zweiten Formgebuugs-Werkzeug (90), worin das erste Formgebungs-Werkzeug (60) eine Oberfläche (62) aufweist, die mindestens so lang und breit ist, wie das Kernelement (30), und worin das zweite Formgebungs-Werkzeug eine Oberfläche aufweist, die mindestens so lang und so breit ist, wie das Kernelement (30) und worin das zweite Formgebungs-Werkzeug (90) ein Profil (82, 86) aufweist, das komplementär ist zu den Merkmalen der mindestens einen Oberfläche (32) des Kernelements (30); und
Halten des Stapels zwischen dem ersten und zweiten Formgebungs-Werkzeug (60 und 90) bis der Stapel auskühlt und sich zwischen Bereichen den Kernelements (30) und der Lage (20), während sie miteinander in Kontakt stehen, Bindungen ausbilden;
dadurch gekennzeichnet, dass das Volumen eines konvexen Bereichs des Kernelements (30) größer ist als das Volumen eines konkaven Bereichs des zweiten Formgebungs-Werkzeuges, das komplementär ist zu dem konvexen Bereich des Kernelements (30).

A method of forming articles including a shape defining compressible core member (30), and a thermoplastic external shell, said method comprising the steps of:
providing a shape defining compressible core member (30) including a first surface (32) and a second surface (34), wherein at least one surface (32, 34) includes a pattern of features;
positioning said core member (30) adjacent to a first heated pliable thermoplastic sheet (20) to form a stack including said first sheet (20) and said core member (30), wherein said first pliable thermoplastic sheet (20) is longer and wider than said core member (30);
compressing said stack between a first molding tool (60), and a second molding tool (90), wherein said first molding tool (60) has a surface (62) at least as long and as wide as said core member (30), and said second molding tool has a surface at least as long and as wide as said core member (30) and that said second molding tool (90) has a contour (82, 86) complementary to the features of said at least one surface (32) of said core member (30); and
holding said stack between said first and said second molding tools (60 and 90) until said stack cools and forms bonds between portions of said core member (30) and said sheet (20) while in contact with one another,
characterised in that the volume of a convex portion of said core member (30) is larger than the volume of a concave portion of said second molding tool complementary to the convex portion of said core member (30).
